						&lt;td class=&#34;crayon-code&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;crayon-pre&#34; style=&#34;font-size: 15px !important; line-height: 20px !important; -moz-tab-size:4; -o-tab-size:4; -webkit-tab-size:4; tab-size:4;&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;crayon-line&#34; id=&#34;crayon-5fba44837f5e3413977136-1&#34;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;crayon-line&#34; id=&#34;crayon-5fba44837f5e3413977136-2&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-t&#34;&gt;interface&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-h&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-e&#34;&gt;Person&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-h&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-sy&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;crayon-line&#34; id=&#34;crayon-5fba44837f5e3413977136-3&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-h&#34;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-v&#34;&gt;name&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-o&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-h&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-t&#34;&gt;string&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-sy&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;crayon-line&#34; id=&#34;crayon-5fba44837f5e3413977136-4&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-h&#34;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-v&#34;&gt;age&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-o&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-h&#34;&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-t&#34;&gt;integer&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-sy&#34;&gt;;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;crayon-line&#34; id=&#34;crayon-5fba44837f5e3413977136-5&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;crayon-sy&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;crayon-line&#34; id=&#34;crayon-5fba44837f5e3413977136-6&#34;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
					&lt;/tr&gt;
				&lt;/tbody&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
			&lt;/div&gt;
		&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;!-- [Format Time: 0.0005 seconds] --&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;It is easily possible and common to mix and match these two usage patterns.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;BuckleScript strives to clearly distinguish between these two usage patterns. For dictionary style usage, &lt;a target=&#34;_blank&#34; href=&#34;https://bucklescript.github.io/docs/en/object.html#object-as-hash-map&#34;&gt;JS.Dict&lt;/a&gt; is preferred. And for Record style usage BuckleScript provides a wrapper to be used in conjuction with Object types.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2&gt;ReasonML Object Type&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;To see an example of object types, let us look an a translated example of stack object type from &lt;a target=&#34;_blank&#34; href=&#34;https://realworldocaml.org/v1/en/html/objects.html#ocaml-objects&#34;&gt;Real world OCaml&lt;/a&gt;:&lt;/p&gt;
